æntæ dæ mærdtæ ʒeneti</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>да будут твои покойники в раю</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>may your dead be in paradise</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Gurdž._Æduli"/><biblScope>93</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><etym xml:lang="ru">Из <mentioned xml:lang="ar"><lang/><w>jannat</w><gloss><q>рай</q></gloss></mentioned>. В ходу у мусульманских народов: <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>jannat</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="tr"><lang/><w>ǯennet</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lez"><lang/><w>ǯennet</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/><w>ženet</w></mentioned> и др.%n<bibl corresp="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"><biblScope>II 79</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl corresp="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."><biblScope>9</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">From <mentioned xml:lang="ar"><lang/><w>jannat</w><gloss><q>paradise</q></gloss></mentioned>. It is in use among Muslim peoples: <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>jannat</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="tr"><lang/><w>ǯennet</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lez"><lang/><w>ǯennet</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/><w>ženet</w></mentioned> etc.%n<bibl corresp="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"><biblScope>II 79</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl corresp="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."><biblScope>9</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry>